name: Kedai Kopi Q~ta
address: Des. Melaya Krajan, Jl. Raya Denpasar - Gilimanuk, Melaya, Kec. Melaya, Kabupaten Jembrana, Bali 82252, Indonesia
review 1:
I stayed at Melaya Cabanas nearby, which Pak Nyoman (the owner of this cafe) is the caretaker of the place. I ordered food from Kedai Kopi Q~ta for breakfast, my husband really liked the Nasi Goreng Kambing. I ordered Toasted Bread with sprinkles and it was nice too. The orange juice was from a real orange.
I also stopped by this cafe while waiting for the bus to Denpasar. Bu Nyoman and Pak Nyoman were really kind. They gave us snacks and a cup of water while we waited, and we had a nice chat with them, too. Pak Nyoman was roasting coffee beans which smelled verrry good. My husband bought their ground coffee and he said it was real tasty, and the price was inexpensive!
Being in their cafe really makes you feel welcomed by the locals, which treat you warmly like you were their own old friend.

Thank you Pak&Bu Nyoman, and Kak Dyas (their son)!
review 2:
It is an awesome little cafe with great atmosphere. Owners are very passionate about what they do.
Come and try local coffee & food and especially Balinese hospitality :)
Glad we popped in.
review 3: Nice Cafe, really good Coffee, delicious food and lovely owners! We loved the soup ikan and fresh crabs (special menu of the day when we were there). Also fried shrimps were so good! Nice atmosphere :)
review 4: Fantastic food and service by Pak Nyoman and Ibu Elizabeth
